	<h1>About</h1>

	<p class="one-line">OpenSit is a place where people who meditate can record their experiences and connect with each other.</p>

	<p>More and more of us are turning to meditation as a way of bringing wisdom, happiness and peace into our lives. Millions of individuals, along with a growing body of scientific research, are recognising the potential for meditation to <strong>train our minds and change our brains</strong>.

	<p>I built OpenSit through my own passion for meditation. I have been sitting for half a decade, after discovering meditation through the <a href="https://www.buddhistgeeks.com/2011/06/the-core-features-of-pragmatic-dharma/">Pragmatic Dharma movement</a>.

	<p>This is a new movement that is refining and improving the core technology of meditation so that anyone can understand and radically alter their own levels of well-being, without having to wade through religious myths or spiritual gurus:

	<blockquote>"...a movement that seeks to preserve core meditation technology and supports, integrate helpful aspects from across traditions, refine the techniques and maps through exploration and verification, and spread the message that it can be done. It is also a movement to strip away the aspects of dogma, ritual,rigid hierarchy, myth and falsehood that hinder high-level practice and keep the culture of meditation mired in unhelpful taboos and misplaced effort."</blockquote>

	<p>This movement towards transparency and honesty naturally emphasises <strong>practice over belief</strong>. Journalling your practice is a great way to reflect on your own journey, and leaves interesting trails for others to study. OpenSit is firmly built around the practice journal, with an added social element so that you can follow other peoples journals.</p>

	<p><strong>The culture surrounding meditation is evolving</strong>. OpenSit is community exploring the ways in which think about practice in a globalised world, the ways we can support each other, and the effects of meditation itself, from equanimity, to energetics to enlightenment.</p>

	<h2>Our Principles</h2>
	<p class="one-line">We're all about <strong>building a community</strong> around <strong>authentic meditation</strong>, fuelled by our <strong>desire to awaken</strong>.</p>

	<p>Sincerity over seriousness and spiritualising. whether our lives are great, horrendous or boring, what matters is our sincerity to know things as they are.</p>

	<p>Recognising that we all have the POTENTIAL to WAKE UP



